Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.61,0:00:26.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我到这里的旅程从登上联盟号飞船开始\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}My journey here aboard a Soyuz spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.17,0:00:31.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从哈萨克斯坦起飞到对接完成差不多花了5小时\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}from lift-off in Kazakhstan to the time we docked just took over about 5 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.61,0:00:38.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}接下来的视频会包含一些入轨后飞船内部拍摄的片段\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The video you are about to see contains some unique footage taken inside the capsule while it is in orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.36,0:00:42.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}视频也会解释联盟号如何安全入轨以及与对接国际空间站对接\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and explains how the Soyuz safely reaches orbit and docks to the Space Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.40,0:00:45.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其他很多宇航员也经历了相同的旅程\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Many other astronauts have taken the same journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.72,0:00:50.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们也会在这个视频里分享他们的经历\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and some of them will also share their experience with you in this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.00,0:00:51.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}看得开心:)\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Have fun watching it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.21,0:01:05.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}9分钟前 联盟号飞船从哈萨克斯坦的拜科努尔发射场起飞进入轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Nine minutes ago, a Soyuz spacecraft blasted into orbit from Baikonur in Kazakhstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.93,0:01:10.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它现在绕着地球飞行 速度是喷气飞机的30倍\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It is now speeding around the Earth thirty times faster than a jumbo jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.13,0:01:13.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它只有一个目标 追上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It has a single purpose: to catch up with,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.05,0:01:19.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并交会对接 离地400km某处的国际空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}rendezvous, and dock with the International Space Station located somewhere 400 km above the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.19,0:01:25.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}宇航员刚刚完成了发射时序的最后一步\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The astronauts just went through the last phase of the launch sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.90,0:01:28.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号飞船与火箭的分离\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the separation of the Soyuz spacecraft from the rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.76,0:01:44.28,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}之后立刻 当然了 你漂浮起来\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And immediately afterwards, of course, you float.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.49,0:01:52.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你可以看看窗外\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}You can look outside the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.96,0:01:56.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你第一次从上空看见地球壮丽的景象\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}you see this magnificent Earth for the first time from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.14,0:01:57.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这种感觉相当好\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It's really a great feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.31,0:02:12.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在 他们首次进入环地轨道 进入高度约220公里\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Now in their first orbits around Earth at an insertion altitude of about 220 km,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.07,0:02:16.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号上的三名宇航员当然有着绝妙的视野\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the three astronauts in the Soyuz certainly have a wonderful view.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.83,0:02:20.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是还有工作要做\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But there is work to be done,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.19,0:02:25.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为他们离国际空间站还有几百公里的距离 他们的最终目的地\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}as they are still hundreds of kilometres away from the ISS -- their final destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.10,0:02:34.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}国际空间站于1998年开始运行\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The International Space Station began life in 1998
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.70,0:02:38.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}此后大约每90分钟绕地球运行一次\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and has been orbiting Earth about once every 90 minutes ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.55,0:02:44.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}国际空间站的轨道平面是相当固定的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The orbital plane of the ISS is fairly constant,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.08,0:02:46.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而地球总是在自转\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}while the Earth is always rotating.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.65,0:02:51.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}把国际空间站的轨道投影到二维地图上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Projecting the orbit of the ISS onto a 2D map,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.00,0:02:53.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们可以看到一系列相交的曲线\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}we see a series of intersecting curves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.73,0:03:17.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}虽然在技术上可以在任何时候发射联盟号火箭\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}While it is technically possible to launch the Soyuz rocket at any time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.59,0:03:24.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但在ISS轨道经过哈萨克斯坦的拜科努尔航天发射场后不久 进行发射的效率最高\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}it's most efficient to do so shortly after the ISS orbit passes over the Baikonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.66,0:03:29.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就缩短了与空间站交会对接的时间\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}This shortens the amount of time to rendezvous and dock with the Station
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.39,0:03:32.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从两天左右缩短到6个小时\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}from about two days to only six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.85,0:03:36.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这种短时交会轨道自2013年开始实施\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}This short rendezvous trajectory has been implemented since 2013.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.59,0:03:41.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然而 如果联盟号火箭错过了必要的发射窗口\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}However, if the Soyuz rocket misses the necessary launch window
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.56,0:03:44.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}或接下来任何的发动机点火不能按计划进行\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}or any of the upcoming engine burns do not occur as planned,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.28,0:03:50.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}航天器有足够的多余燃料 可以恢复到两天的长时交会对接\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the spacecraft has enough extra fuel to revert to a two-day long rendezvous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.90,0:04:00.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}交会被重新规划为过去使用的长时轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and thus, the rendezvous was replanned to the formerly used long trajectory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.83,0:04:05.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你要考虑到这有一定的风险\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}You take into consideration that there are some risks,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.76,0:04:07.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有的风险比其他的更严重\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}some are worse than others,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.21,0:04:13.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}包括从快速对接过渡到长时对接的可能性\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}including the possibility of transitioning from a very short docking to a long docking,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.36,0:04:16.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是一年前的标准\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}which was the standard until a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.41,0:04:21.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们知道这种可能性 这是我们为之训练的东西\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}We know of the possibility; it's something that we are trained for.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.03,0:04:24.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们知道航天器上有我们这两天所需要的一切\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}We know that the spacecraft has everything that we need for those two days,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.02,0:04:27.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们也知道如何应对\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and we know how to react.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.93,0:04:30.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}交会的定义是\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Rendezvous is defined
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.08,0:04:35.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}两个空间飞行器相互接近的一系列机动动作\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}as the sequence of manoeuvres governing the approach of two space vehicles to one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.46,0:04:41.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在大多数情况下 其中一个是追逐者 执行机动 在这种情况下 是联盟号\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}In most cases one of them is the chaser, performing the manoeuvres, in this case, the Soyuz,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.06,0:04:48.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而第二个是被动目标飞行器 在这种情况下是国际空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}while the second is a passive target vehicle, in this case, the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.40,0:04:54.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}理想情况下，两个飞行器在预选的空间和时间上准确安全地相遇\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Ideally, both vehicles meet up safely at an exact preselected point in space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.41,0:04:59.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但联盟号是如何实现的呢？\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But how does the Soyuz achieve this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.32,0:05:03.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号必须从最初的进入高度爬升\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Well, the Soyuz has to climb from its initial insertion altitude
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.24,0:05:08.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}到与空间站相同的高度 然后进入并停留在这个轨道上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}up to the same altitude of the Station, and then join and stay on this orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.36,0:05:12.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这听起来是一个足够简单的任务\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It sounds like a simple enough task,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.37,0:05:16.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这不可能从开始的进入高度 只用一次机动就完成\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}but it cannot be done in one single manoeuvre starting from the insertion altitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.95,0:05:22.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最终对接的计算是基于联盟号精确的初始高度的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Calculations for the final docking are based on a precise initial Soyuz altitude
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.83,0:05:27.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}遗憾的是 我们事先不知道确切的进入轨道高度\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and unfortunately, the exact insertion orbit altitude is not known in advance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.87,0:05:30.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是由于火箭发射过程中存在一些不可预测性\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}because of some unpredictability in the rocket launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.53,0:05:36.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 会使用两次机动的方式 其间有一个中间调相轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Therefore, two manoeuvres are used with an intermediate phasing orbit in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.88,0:05:41.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}相位调整轨道是最终对接计算的基础\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The phasing orbit is the basis for the final docking calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.96,0:05:55.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在霍曼转移过程中 联盟号要使用两次发动机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}During the Hohmann transfer, the Soyuz has to use its engines twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.98,0:06:01.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}第一次是在发射后不久离开目前的进入轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The first time is to leave its current insertion orbit shortly after launch
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.73,0:06:03.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并上升转移到调相轨道上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and transfer up to the phasing orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.01,0:06:09.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}第二次是让飞行器以适当的速度飞行 使其保持在那个轨道上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The second time is to get the vehicle traveling at the right speed to stay on that orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.48,0:06:18.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}调相轨道比国际空间站轨道低100公里左右 它的作用非常特殊\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The phasing orbit is lower than the ISS orbit by about 100 km and it serves a very specific purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.20,0:06:26.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它减少了相位角 或者说两个航天器在各自轨道上的相位角\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It decreases the phasing angle, or the angle between the two spacecraft in their respective orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.19,0:06:30.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这里我们看到联盟号在相位调整轨道上运行 用黄色的颜色标明\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Here we see the Soyuz orbiting in the phasing orbit, depicted in yellow,
