Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.00,0:06:41.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}第三个红色轨道是联盟号已经离开的进入轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The third red orbit is the insertion orbit the Soyuz has already left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.80,0:06:46.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}由于联盟号在较低的轨道上 它的飞行速度会比空间站快\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Because the Soyuz is on a lower orbit it will travel faster than the Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.61,0:06:51.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 联盟号利用这个调相轨道追赶国际空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Therefore, the Soyuz uses this phasing orbit to catch up with the ISS.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.43,0:06:57.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}根据使用的是长时交会还是短时交会\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Depending on whether the long or short rendezvous approach is being used,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.54,0:07:03.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号将在这个调相轨道上停留近两天或仅仅几个小时\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the Soyuz will remain in this phasing orbit for close to two days, or just a few hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.33,0:07:06.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}无论达到所需的相位角需要多长时间\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}however long it takes to reach the desired phasing angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.10,0:07:14.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同一时间 宇航员还不只是享受美景和失重\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Meanwhile, the crew haven't just been enjoying the views and weightlessness,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.52,0:07:19.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们一直在忙着查漏补缺 确保系统正常运行\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}they've been busy with leak checks and making sure systems are performing nominally.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.17,0:07:23.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后他们发出对接探针伸出的命令\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Then they issue the command for docking probe extension
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:26.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为最后的对接时序做提前准备\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}in advanced preparation for the final docking sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.78,0:07:31.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只要确认了飞船的气压完好\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}As soon as the pressure integrity of the vehicle is confirmed,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.10,0:07:36.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}任务控制中心就会发出指令 让宇航员松开安全带\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the Mission Control Centre gives the go-ahead for the crew to loosen their seatbelts,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.53,0:07:38.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}打开头盔 脱掉手套\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}open their helmets, and take off their gloves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.56,0:07:44.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}到达调相轨道后\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Once they reach the phasing orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.35,0:07:47.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}宇航员们终于有了一些应得的休息时间\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the crew finally have some well-deserved downtime,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.48,0:07:51.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}特别是那些完成了为期两天的长时交会的人\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}especially those completing the two-day long rendezvous trajectory.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:54.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们所说的五个耳聋轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}There are what we call five deaf orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.85,0:07:59.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是5个其上宇航员不能与地面联系的轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It's five orbits in which the crew cannot have contact with the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.19,0:08:04.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是因为联盟号飞船的轨道没有经过俄罗斯的上空\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}because the orbit of the Soyuz is not passing over Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.20,0:08:07.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只有当你与联盟号经过俄罗斯上空时 你才能与地面接触\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and you only have contact with the ground when you're passing over Russia with the Soyuz.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.79,0:08:09.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以你只能完全靠自己\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So you are completely on yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.62,0:08:13.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以对于宇航员来说 这其实是个很不错的时候 因为你不会被打扰\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So it's actually a nice time for the crew, because you cannot be disturbed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.19,0:08:16.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}没有人能给你任务 你想做什么就做什么\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}nobody can give you tasks, you can do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.17,0:08:19.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}幸运的是 对宇航员来说\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Luckily for the astronauts,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.76,0:08:24.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号的设计让他们在整个旅程中不用被限制在座位上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the Soyuz is designed so they are not confined to their seats for the entire trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.22,0:08:30.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号虽然小 但可以让宇航员在可进入的舱室之间自由移动\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Though small, the spacecraft allows the astronauts to move freely between the accessible modules.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.81,0:08:42.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号有三个舱段 轨道舱\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The Soyuz has three compartments: the Orbital Module,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.02,0:08:44.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}返回舱 以及设备舱\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the Descent Module, and the Instrument Compartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.35,0:08:49.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}每个舱段都有不同的结构 也有特定的用途\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Each compartment has a different architecture, and a specific purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.53,0:08:53.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}轨道舱 也就是生活舱\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The Orbital Module, or living compartment,
