Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.58,0:09:01.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在我们在联盟号上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So here we are in the Soyuz.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.81,0:09:12.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以我们尽可能不去使用它\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}so we try not to use it too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.41,0:09:15.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这里面有饮用水 如果我们需要喝水的话\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It has drinking water in it if we need something to drink,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.49,0:09:20.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后当然 它为我们装了很多货物\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and then, of course, it's filled up with a lot of cargo for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.06,0:09:23.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}设备舱 宇航员无法进入\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The Instrument Compartment, not accessible to the astronauts,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.85,0:09:26.46,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}里面有氧气罐和推进剂罐\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}houses the oxygen and propellant tanks,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.46,0:09:29.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}推进器 机载计算机和一些传感器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}thrusters, the on-board computer, and a number of sensors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.16,0:09:32.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从返回舱中\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}From the Descent Module,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.87,0:09:37.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}三名宇航员监控着有关航天器和国际空间站的所有信息\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the three crewmembers monitor all information about the spacecraft and the ISS
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.55,0:09:39.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}包括地面数据 机载计算机\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}from ground data, the on-board computers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.04,0:09:44.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以及一个安装在外部的潜望镜的光学视角\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and an optical display of the view from a periscope mounted on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.31,0:09:51.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在第二次轨道转移和最后的交会对接中\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}For the second orbital transfer and the final rendezvous manoeuvres,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.07,0:09:53.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}宇航员返回到这个舱内的座位上\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the astronauts return to their seats in this module.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.81,0:10:00.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}第二次轨道转移将联盟号从调相轨道上升到国际空间站轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The second orbital transfer brings the Soyuz from the phasing orbit up to the ISS orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.61,0:10:07.39,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就是双椭圆转移 需要三次发动机点火 而不是霍曼转移的两次\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It's called a bielliptic transfer, and requires three engine burns instead of the Hohmann's two.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.39,0:10:13.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从调相轨道出发 前两次点火将联盟号送上国际空间站轨道\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}From the phasing orbit, the first two burns bring the Soyuz up to the ISS orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.77,0:10:39.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这里用双椭圆转移而不是霍曼转移的原因是\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The reason for using a bielliptic transfer here instead of the Hohmann's is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.32,0:10:44.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号不仅可以在国际空间站附近达到正确的高度\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}that the Soyuz will not only reach the correct altitude in the close vicinity of the ISS,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.33,0:10:47.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还能以准确的速度到达国际空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}but also with exactly the desired speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.15,0:10:52.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管有这些精确的机动\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Despite these precise manoeuvres,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.06,0:10:55.83,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但如果推进器未能使联盟号减速\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}what if the thrusters fail to slow down the Soyuz
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.87,0:10:59.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而它在接近国际空间站时飞行速度过快怎么办？\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and the vehicle travels too fast as it approaches the ISS?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.63,0:11:05.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这可能是个灾难性的结局 联盟号不是对接 而是撞上了空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}This could end in disaster, with the Soyuz crashing into the Station instead of docking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.15,0:11:09.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为了防止这种情况的发生 联盟号进行了一次额外的侧向点火\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}To prevent this from happening the Soyuz performs an additional side burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.95,0:11:17.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这样一来 它的轨道平面稍有变化 两飞行器之间就不可能发生碰撞\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}This changes its orbital plane slightly and makes a collision between the two vehicles impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.72,0:11:19.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在整个交会对接过程中\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Throughout the rendezvous process,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.59,0:11:26.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号机载计算机不断确定联盟号本身和国际空间站的位置和速度\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the Soyuz on-board computer continually determines the position and velocity of the Soyuz itself and of the ISS.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.06,0:11:30.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为此 它使用地面测控提供的测量结果\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}To do so, it uses measurements provided by the ground controllers
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.79,0:11:33.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}和一个叫Kurs的雷达系统\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and a radar system called the Kurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.99,0:11:34.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这样一来\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}In this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.86,0:11:40.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}交会期间的所有点火都由机载计算机计算并自动完成\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}all of the burns during the rendezvous are calculated and automated by the on-board computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:48.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号使用特殊的雷达系统在太空中导航并寻找空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So Soyuz navigates in space and looks for the Station with a special radar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.57,0:11:50.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这个系统叫做Kurs\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}which is called the Kurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.32,0:11:54.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这在离空间站400km的地方就会被打开\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}This gets turned on at 400 km from the Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:55.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它找啊找啊找\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It looks, looks, looks,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.38,0:12:01.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一般情况下 会在180公里左右看见并锁定空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and usually it sees the Station and locks into the Station at around, more or less, 180 kilometres.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.52,0:12:04.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在这个距离 我们事实上看不到空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}At that distance, we really don't see the Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.21,0:12:10.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它可能 即使你能看到它 它可能和太空中的任何一颗恒星都很相似\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It's probably -- even if you could see it, it's probably similar to any of the stars that are up there in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:17.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但你在屏幕上看到 那个锁定标志 软件显示雷达锁定了空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But you see on the screen the lock, the software indication that the radar locked into the Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.76,0:12:30.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当你正常点火时\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}When you do a normal burn,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.91,0:12:35.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞行器以每秒两度的速度旋转到正确的姿态\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the vehicle rotates to the correct attitude at two degrees per second,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.12,0:12:39.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后大约8分钟后开始点火\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and then it takes about eight minutes to start the burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.27,0:12:41.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当你接近空间站时 你必须要减速\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}When you're close to the Space Station and you have to brake,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.73,0:12:43.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然这样是不行的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}of course this would not work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.50,0:12:46.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以飞行器突然间开始快速旋转\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So then the vehicle all of a sudden starts rotating quite fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.90,0:12:50.09,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一秒三度半 紧接着\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}three and a half degrees per second and only just after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.09,0:12:52.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}50秒之后 你就已经开始点火\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}50 seconds after that you already have the burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.90,0:12:54.63,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而一旦点火完成后\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And once the burn is completed,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.63,0:12:58.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞行器立即又开始向正常方向旋转\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}immediately the vehicle starts rotating again to the normal orientation,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.70,0:13:01.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}宇航员必须对此进行相当严格的监控\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and the crew has to monitor this quite intensely
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.84,0:13:05.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}去看一切是否正常真的是工作量的高峰\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and these are really high peaks of workload to see that everything is okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.61,0:13:07.09,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}旋转还算顺利\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the rotation is going okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.09,0:13:10.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你知道你点火了 点火数值没问题\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}you know that you have the burn, the burn values were okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.99,0:13:14.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你旋转回去 然后在你的主显示屏上看到空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}you rotate back, and then you see back the Space Station in your main display.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.83,0:13:20.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们可以看到 先是一个点 比天空中的其他星星亮了一点\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}We could see it, first a dot a little bit brighter than the other stars in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.70,0:13:22.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后一点一点地\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and then little by little,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.65,0:13:28.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们开始看到像小蜘蛛一样的 那些太阳能阵列和其他所有东西\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}we start to see like a little spider first with all the solar arrays and everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.36,0:13:34.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后很清楚地 有个巨大的物体出现在我们眼前\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and then it was apparent that there's a huge outpost right there in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.97,0:13:38.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在这个阶段 坐在中间的指令长\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}During this stage, the crew commander, sitting in the middle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.52,0:13:41.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}向同伴发布重要信息和指令\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}gives vital information and instructions to his crewmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.98,0:13:48.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们的工作量增加了 许多参数需要检查 许多系统需要激活\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Their workload has increased; many parameters need to be checked and systems activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.89,0:13:50.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}发射前几天\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Days before launch,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.28,0:13:54.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}莫斯科和休斯顿飞行任务控制中心的飞行动力学专家小组\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}a team of flight dynamics experts at the Mission Control Centres in Moscow and Houston
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.89,0:13:58.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}确定了国际空间站的理想位置和方向\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}determine the ideal position and orientation of the ISS,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.75,0:14:01.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}基于对制约因素的仔细分析\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}based on a careful analysis of the constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.47,0:14:05.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些因素可能会影响交会对接时间线上的最后步骤\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}that could affect these final stages of the rendezvous timeline.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.64,0:14:09.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}首先 对接时必须有足够的照明条件\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}First, there must be adequate lighting conditions at the time of docking
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.24,0:14:14.39,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这样 联盟号上的宇航员就可以看到国际空间站 而不会由于太阳而暂时失明或被遮挡\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}so that the Soyuz crew can see the ISS without being blinded or blocked by the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.11,0:14:18.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}要看空间站是否有光照 是否在阳光下\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It depends if the Station is illuminated, is in the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.30,0:14:21.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么即使距离相对较远也能看到它\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}then you can see it even if you are relatively far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.79,0:14:26.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 如果空间站不在阳光下 那么即使离得再近也看不到它\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}But if the Station is not in the sun, then you cannot see it even if you are close.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.67,0:14:30.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}此外 必须避免ISS部件过大的温度波动\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Additionally, major temperature fluctuations of ISS elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.89,0:14:35.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如太阳能阵列等 以防止结构变形\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}such as the solar arrays, must be avoided to prevent structural deformation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.18,0:14:42.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最后 地面 联盟号和国际空间站之间必须有通畅的通信线路\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Finally, there must be clear communication pathways between the ground, Soyuz, and ISS.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.53,0:14:48.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}交会是由机载计算机执行的一个完全自动化的过程\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The rendezvous is a fully automated process performed by the on-board computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.03,0:14:52.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 指令长仍旧拿着手动控制器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}However, the commander still takes the hand controller
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.09,0:14:56.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以防万一需要进行应急手动对接\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4} just in case there is a need to perform a contingency manual docking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.60,0:14:59.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果你没有看到空间站 或者在那一刻发生了什么事情\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}If you don't see the Space Station or something happens at that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.13,0:15:02.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么你可能就需要手动控制了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}then you might have to take manual control.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.25,0:15:05.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以你要牢牢记住空间站现在在哪里\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And so you have to remember very well, where is the Space Station now,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.54,0:15:07.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我要采取什么行动\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}what are the actions that I'm going to take,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.71,0:15:10.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这才是真正的紧张时刻\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and this is really the intense moments that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.19,0:15:15.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}手动对接需要两个手动控制器来驾驶飞行器\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Manual docking requires two hand controllers to pilot the vehicle,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.32,0:15:20.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}左边的控制平移 右边的控制旋转\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}a left one that control translation and a right one that controls rotation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.92,0:15:24.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}航天员们都经过了彻底的手动对接培训\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The crew are thoroughly trained in these manual docking procedures,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.41,0:15:28.46,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}甚至在拜科努尔的发射前最后几天都会进行练习\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}even training until the very last days before launch in Baikonur.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.98,0:15:32.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}除了应急对接\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Besides contingency docking,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.69,0:15:37.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}宇航员们还可以将他们的手动控制训练应用在重新对接的机动中\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the crew might also utilize their manual control training during redocking manoeuvres.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.73,0:15:44.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}国际空间站不断有载人的联盟号飞船和其他无人驾驶的补给飞船到来\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The ISS is constantly visited by manned Soyuz vehicles and other unmanned supply ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.04,0:15:49.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有时需要将对接的的联盟号分离\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Sometimes it is necessary to undock an attached Soyuz
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.09,0:15:55.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}将其重新停靠到国际空间站的另一个对接口 为新飞船腾出空间\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and redock it to another port on the ISS to make room for one of these new ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.89,0:15:59.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Luca Parmitano 在第37远征队任务中做了此事\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Luca Parmitano did this as part of Expedition 37.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.76,0:16:07.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我的队员是为数不多能进行人工对接的宇航员之一 整个对接过程非常顺利\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}My crew was one of the few crews able to perform a manual docking and it went very smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.75,0:16:11.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们很兴奋 因为这是我们训练了很久的东西 而且我们有能力做到这一点\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}We were excited because it's something that we trained on for a long time and we were able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.24,0:16:16.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}除了这种情况外 常规的对接程序是全自动的\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Apart from this case, a routine docking sequence is fully automated
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.56,0:16:21.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}宇航员的主要任务是监控系统 确保程序正常运行\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and the crew's main task is to monitor the systems to ensure nominal procedures.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.00,0:16:28.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在这个常规对接过程的阶段中 飞行器的相对速度不断降低\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}At this stage during routine docking the vehicle's relative speed continues to decrease,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.45,0:16:30.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}两者之间的距离也会不断缩短\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}as does the distance between the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.32,0:16:34.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在距离空间站400米的地方 新的阶段开始了\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}400 metres from the Space Station, a new phase enters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.89,0:16:37.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就是我们所说的绕飞阶段\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}This is the phase what we call fly-around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.77,0:16:42.83,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在这个阶段 飞行器实际上并没有对准所需的对接端口\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}During this phase, the vehicle is actually not pointing at the desired docking port,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.83,0:16:46.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而是对准了空间站的任意一个Kurs天线\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}but at either one of the Station's Kurs antennas.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.37,0:16:50.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只有当飞行器到达150米的位置保持模式时\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}It's only when the vehicle reaches its 150m station keeping mode
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.06,0:16:55.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}方向才会改变为指向所选的对接端口\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}that the orientation changes to point at the selected docking port instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.88,0:17:00.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后联盟号进行第二次绕飞 对准对接端口\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The Soyuz then performs a second fly-around to align up with the docking port
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.41,0:17:03.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时保持150米的距离\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}while keeping a distance of 150 m.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.72,0:17:05.63,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一旦对准了对接端口\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Once aligned with the docking port,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.73,0:17:09.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}宇航员发出最后一个阶段的指令 最后进近\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}the crew issues the command for the last stage: the final approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.79,0:17:15.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号计算机显示器利用Kurs的数据为航天员提供\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The Soyuz computer display uses data from Kurs to provide the astronauts
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.36,0:17:19.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有关交会对接的相关信息\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}with pertinent information about the rendezvous and docking manoeuvres.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.72,0:17:23.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在其他读数中 与国际空间站的距离有被显示\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Among other read-outs, the distance from the ISS is displayed,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.56,0:17:25.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这里显示的是5m\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}here showing five metres,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.40,0:17:36.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}用于跟踪目标的对齐\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}used to track alignment of the target.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.13,0:17:54.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一旦探针碰到对接舱门的入口锥体 就会发生接触\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Contact occurs as soon as the probe touches the entrance cone of the docking hatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.37,0:17:58.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后推进器给了联盟号一个额外的推动力\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Then the thrusters give the Soyuz an extra push,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.48,0:18:00.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对接机构确保了捕获\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and the docking mechanism ensures capture.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.44,0:18:20.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我想这就是碰撞的地方\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}I think this is where the impact was.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.96,0:18:28.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以我觉得是偏离中心4到5英寸左右\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So I would say about four to five inches off-centre.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.99,0:18:31.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对于经过了几百万英里来说相当不错\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Pretty good after traveling for a couple million miles!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.72,0:18:36.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}探针缩回 两架飞行器就会更架接近对方\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The probe retracts, and you get the two vehicles closer to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.46,0:18:38.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后当它们之间的距离很近的时候\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and then when they are very close to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.62,0:18:41.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不到两三毫米 钩子就开始合拢\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}less than two to three millimetres, the hooks start closing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.71,0:18:45.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而当这些钩子完全闭合时 就会承受巨大的压力\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And it's when these hooks are fully closed that can take an enormous pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.26,0:18:50.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为每一个钩子可以承受16吨的力\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}because they can withstand 16 tonnes of force, each of the hooks,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.71,0:18:53.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而你在联盟号飞船上有8个钩子\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and you have eight hooks on the Soyuz vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.89,0:18:57.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这样做还是不够 因为O型环里面可能会有东西\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}This is still not enough, because there might be something inside the O-rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.89,0:19:04.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一些污垢或者是一些杂物 这些都会使密封性不好\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}some dirt or some debris, that is not allowing for a good seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.11,0:19:12.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以会高精度地进行一系列相应的真空和减压的工作\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}So there is a series of vacuum and depressurisations done in a very astute manner
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.43,0:19:18.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可以验证每一个隔间是否真的密封严密\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}that verifies that each one of these compartments is actually sealed tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.04,0:19:26.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只有在这时 顺便说一下 这一切都需要一个小时 一到两个小时\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Only at that point -- and by the way, all of this takes I would say an hour, one to two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.08,0:19:32.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只有当一切都被证明是完全密封的时候\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Only then when everything is proved to be fully sealed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.29,0:19:36.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只有这样 你才能打开空间站的舱门 联盟号的舱门\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}only then you can open the hatch of the Station, the hatch of the Soyuz,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.34,0:19:38.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}宇航员们才能真正进入太空站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}and the crew can actually go into the Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.28,0:19:45.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们通常要做的就是敲空间站一侧的舱门\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And what we usually do is we knock on the hatch that goes on the side of the Space Station,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.97,0:19:49.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们敲回来 我们知道那边有人\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}they knock back; we know that there is somebody else on the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.59,0:19:53.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而联盟号飞船和国际空间站之间的舱门\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}And the hatches between the Soyuz spacecraft and the International Space Station
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.87,0:19:57.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在中央时间11点14分开放\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}opening at 11:14 PM Central Time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.33,0:20:00.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后是大家的拥抱和微笑\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}Then it's hugs and smiles for everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.73,0:20:09.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}宇航员们现在安全地登上了国际空间站\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}The astronauts are now safely on-board the International Space Station,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.67,0:20:12.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们未来6个月的家\N{\r1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50}{\blur4}their home for the next six months.
Comment: 0,0:00:15.62,0:00:19.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,字幕
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.58,0:02:05.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后 绝美的太阳很快就出现了 照亮 迸发出光辉
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.15,0:12:23.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7s,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}前面提到的双椭圆转移的第三次也是最后一次点火是非常重要的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.08,0:12:28.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7s,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为它为飞行器对接前的近ISS交会程序做好了准备
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.62,0:00:19.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我是Alexander Gerst ESA的宇航员
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.72,0:00:23.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我现在在国际空间站和你们说话
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.32,0:01:37.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}发动机关机的动静相当大
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.28,0:01:49.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你知道 这真的是一种非常好的感觉 是的 我们在太空中 我们发射成功了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.34,0:01:51.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在我们在去空间站的路上
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:03:01.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}莫斯科和休斯敦的任务控制中心不断监测国际空间站的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.79,0:03:06.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并能预测未来任何特定时间内国际空间站在轨道上的预期位置
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.34,0:03:12.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这对于确定联盟号航天器何时发射具有重要意义
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.93,0:03:55.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这发生在2014年3月 由于高度控制问题
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.02,0:05:45.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它是用第一种机动的方式到达的 称为霍曼转移
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.65,0:05:49.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}即以20世纪初一位德国科学家的名字命名的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.06,0:09:06.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就是我们所说的БО 生活舱 俄语中的бытовой отсек
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.50,0:09:10.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它还有一个小浴室 只是没有其他的浴室那么好
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.02,0:10:18.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}第三次点火使飞行器以正确的速度 在国际空间站轨道上停留
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.67,0:10:25.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}双椭圆转移的点火是根据调相轨道的精确高度来计算的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.13,0:10:29.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 如果调相轨道过高或过低的话
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.33,0:10:32.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联盟号不会像预期的那样与国际空间站交会
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.31,0:17:28.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而在接近过程中的相对速度也是如此
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.16,0:17:30.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在显示的是10cm/s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.69,0:17:34.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-7e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些信息和其他信息会叠加在视频源上
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.62,0:00:19.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I am Alexander Gerst an astronaut of the European Space Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.72,0:00:23.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I am talking to you from the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.32,0:01:37.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The finishing of the engine of the shut-down of the engine is pretty strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.28,0:01:49.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's really a very nice feeling that you know yes, we are in space, we had a successful launch,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.34,0:01:51.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}now we are on the way to the Space Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.58,0:02:05.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And then just the absolute beauty of the sun coming up really quickly, illuminating, bursting into flame.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:03:01.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Mission Control Centres in Moscow and Houston constantly monitor the position of the ISS,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.79,0:03:06.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and can predict its expected location in the orbit for any given time in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.34,0:03:12.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is important for determining when the Soyuz spacecraft launches.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.93,0:03:55.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This happened in March of 2014 because of an attitude control problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.02,0:05:45.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It is reached using the first manoeuvre, called a Hohmann transfer,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.65,0:05:49.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}named after a German scientist from the beginning of the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.06,0:09:06.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is what we call the БО, the living compartment, "бытовой отсек" in Russian.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.50,0:09:10.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It also has a little bathroom, it's not as good as the other bathrooms
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.02,0:10:18.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The third burn gets the vehicle traveling at the correct speed to stay in the ISS orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.67,0:10:25.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The burns of the bielliptic transfer are calculated based on the precise altitude of the phasing orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.13,0:10:29.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And consequently, if the phasing orbit is too high or too low
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.33,0:10:32.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the Soyuz will not meet up with the ISS as expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.15,0:12:23.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The third and final burn of the pre-mentioned bielliptic transfer is very important,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.08,0:12:28.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because it sets the vehicle up for its near-ISS rendezvous procedures that will lead to docking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.31,0:17:28.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}as is the relative velocity during the approach,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.16,0:17:30.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}currently 10 cm/s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.69,0:17:34.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-medi-5e,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This and other information is overlaid on the video feed,
